Overview:

This project is an AI-based mining and geological analysis system that automatically identifies minerals from drill core sample images using Machine Learning and Image Processing techniques. The system detects mineral layers, highlights mineral regions, estimates depth, and extracts geological features for faster and more accurate core logging.

Features:
Mineral identification from drill core images
Mineral layer highlighting
Depth estimation
Geological feature extraction
Image preprocessing using OpenCV
Machine Learning-based classification
Frontend and backend integration



Technologies Used:
Python
OpenCV
Scikit-learn
TensorFlow / CNN
Flask
HTML, CSS, JavaScript
NumPy & Pandas

Working Process:
Upload drill core sample image
Preprocess image using OpenCV
Extract mineral features
Predict mineral type using ML model
Highlight mineral layers
Display depth and analysis results


Output:
Detected mineral name
Highlighted mineral regions
Confidence score
Estimated depth
Geological feature report


Applications:
Mining exploration
Geological analysis
Mineral detection
Automated core logging


Future Enhancements:
